item.title: CVE-2019-9696|2024-08-04T21:54:45.459Z -- symantec -- symantec%20vip%20enterprise%20gateway
item.description: Symantec VIP Enterprise Gateway (all versions) may be susceptible to a cross-site scripting (XSS) exploit, which is a type of issue that can enable attackers to inject client-side scripts into web pages viewed by other users. A cross-site scripting vulnerability may be used by attackers to potentially bypass access controls such as the same-origin policy.
